This paper deals with information theory and communication systems, specifically the problem of encoding status update packets to minimize the average age at the receiver node. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves networked systems and communication protocols, which fall under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use of numerical evaluations and optimization techniques suggests a connection to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
